    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-12T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-12T13:00:00-05:00" n="159"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d159">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/868: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Genoa</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Balch</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Genoa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-12T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 12, 1940—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 12—4:16 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>82. After <hi rend="italic">Exochorda</hi> sails tomorrow it is estimated by
                    American Export Line, the United States Line, and the American Consulate <pb
                        facs="0135" n="126" xml:id="pg_126"/> General that there will be between 400
                    and 500 Americans from all parts of Europe to evacuate from Genoa to New York.
                        <hi rend="italic">Excalibur</hi> will arrive at Genoa June 26 three-fourths
                    full and can take from here about 75 additional Americans. Freighters now
                    available in the Mediterranean will accommodate between 50 and 100 mainly from
                    eastern Mediterranean ports. This leaves at least 275 Americans unprovided for
                    and at least 150 Latin Americans urgently requesting accommodations. It is
                    therefore strongly recommended that ship accommodations be arranged. It is
                    impossible for these people to proceed to Lisbon or Bordeaux.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Balch</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
